Package net.rotgruengelb.maple.value

Interface MapleDeep<K>

Type Parameters:
K - the type of the key used to retrieve values
All Known Implementing Classes:
MapleList, MapleMap
public interface MapleDeep<K>
Interface for retrieving values from deeply nested structures within the Maple configuration language.

This interface provides methods to retrieve values by a key of type K and cast them into specific types such as Float, Integer, String, Boolean, MapleMap, or MapleList. If the type does not match the requested type, these methods return null. Default values can also be supplied, avoiding null checks in the code.
